dynamic_clauses.title: Insolvency Declarations
dynamic_clauses.content: That the company has failed the cash flow test under section 95A of the Corporations Act, being unable to pay all debts as and when they become due and payable.

dynamic_clauses.title: Liquidation Resolutions
dynamic_clauses.content: That the company be wound up by way of {liquidation_type} pursuant to sections 491-494 of the Corporations Act 2001 (Cth).

dynamic_clauses.title: Liquidator Appointments
dynamic_clauses.content: That {liquidator_name} (ASIC Registration {liquidator_registration}) be appointed to conduct the winding up of this company in accordance with statutory requirements.

dynamic_clauses.title: Creditor Notifications
dynamic_clauses.content: That publication of the liquidation notice be made in the Government Gazette and local newspaper as required by law.

dynamic_clauses.title: Asset Preservation
dynamic_clauses.content: That all assets of the company be preserved and protected for the benefit of creditors until such time as they are realized by the liquidator.

dynamic_clauses.title: Regulatory Compliance
dynamic_clauses.content: That compliance with all Australian Taxation Office obligations be maintained throughout the liquidation process.

dynamic_clauses.title: Director Powers
dynamic_clauses.content: That the powers of the directors cease upon the appointment of the liquidator, except as may be required to assist the liquidator in the performance of their duties.

dynamic_clauses.title: Cooperation Obligations
dynamic_clauses.content: That ongoing cooperation be maintained with any investigations conducted by the liquidator, ASIC, or other regulatory bodies.

dynamic_clauses.title: Statutory Authorizations
dynamic_clauses.content: That the liquidator be authorized to take all steps necessary to comply with the requirements of the Corporations Act 2001 (Cth) and all other applicable legislation.
